BRIEF BIO OF YOURSELF
A cosmopolitan thinker focused on using new NLP tools to solve real-world problems

PRIOR SPEAKING EXPERIENCE
Yes, during my 3 years as CEO of Pixsy, I had to speak multiple times in front of audiences

SESSION TALK OR TITLE
Predicting Political Sentiment of Text

ABSTRACT OR PAPER
In Germany, classical media institutions have no idea what is going on in the internet. Recently the Tagesschau falsely claimed that 48% of political debates on social media revolve around the AfD. Their analysis was based entirely off Twitter Tweets. Rezo, a young YouTuber, managed to wrong-foot German's largest political party, the CDU, with a single YouTube video. My goal is to shed more light into what is actually happening in German social media. My current project uses NLP algorithms to analyze the political sentiment of German Youtube videos and then show the results to the public.

ELEMENTS OF SURPRISE
- Ice Breaker at beginning
- Plan to go off script
- Ask audience a question
- Maintain high energy

TIPS
1 Know your audience: Who are they, what do they care about?
2 Check how interested the audience is in your topic
3 Keep your eyes focused on your audience
4 Don't read out your speech
5 Practice, practice, practice (recite your speech multiple times)

TEDx: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8S0FDjFBj8o

